{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/deploy-a-ghost-blog-on-github-pages-using-gatsby","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"a9c13a8e-20ee-51c5-a57f-4a8d1147238f","html":"<p>If you want to use Ghost as your cms for hosting a blog on GitHub Pages, you need to have a static site generator. We will be using Gatsby to populate the content from our local Ghost installation and deploy it to GitHub Pages.</p>\n<h3 id=\"prerequisites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-label=\"prerequisites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h3>\n<p>In order to follow this tutorial, you should already have <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Node.js</a> and <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/downloads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Git</a> installed.</p>\n<h3 id=\"generate-blog\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#generate-blog\" aria-label=\"generate blog permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Generate Blog</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install the Ghost-CLI</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install ghost-cli@latest -g</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make 2 new directories to house your blog</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">mkdir blog-ghost blog-gatsby</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Navigate into the new <code class=\"language-text\">blog-ghost</code> directory</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cd blog-ghost</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install Ghost locally</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ghost install local</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Set up your freshly installed local instance of Ghost at <code class=\"language-text\">https://localhost:2368</code>\n(follow the installation instructions)</li>\n<li>\n<p>Navigate into the new <code class=\"language-text\">blog-gatsby</code> directory</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cd ../blog-gatsby</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install the Gatsby-CLI</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install gatsby-cli -g</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-starter-ghost</code> using Gatsby-CLI</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby new . https://github.com/TryGhost/gatsby-starter-ghost.git</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Before customising test run Gatsby</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby develop</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Navigate to <code class=\"language-text\">http://localhost:8000/</code></li>\n<li>Generate Gatsby Integration:\nInside the Ghost Admin Panel at <code class=\"language-text\">https://localhost:2368</code>, go to the “Integrations” screen and click ”+ Add custom integration”</li>\n<li>\n<p>Copy generated “apiUrl” and “contentApiKey” into blog-gatsby/.ghost.json</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">{\n&quot;development&quot;: {\n&quot;apiUrl&quot;: &quot;http://localhost:2368&quot;,\n&quot;contentApiKey&quot;: &quot;&lt;yourContentApiKey&gt;&quot;\n},\n&quot;production&quot;: {\n&quot;apiUrl&quot;: &quot;http://localhost:2368&quot;,\n&quot;contentApiKey&quot;: &quot;&lt;yourContentApiKey&gt;&quot;\n}\n}</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Start Gatsby development</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby develop</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"publish-blog\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#publish-blog\" aria-label=\"publish blog permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Publish Blog</h3>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Build Blog</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby build</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>View production version at <code class=\"language-text\">https://localhost:9000</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby serve</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Integrate Gatsby Blog to GitHub Pages:\nInside <code class=\"language-text\">blog-gatsby/</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install gh-pages</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add GitHub repository name to <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">module.exports = {\npathPrefix: &quot;/&lt;repository_name&gt;&quot;,\n}</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add a custom deploy command to package.json</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">{\n&quot;scripts&quot;: {\n&quot;deploy&quot;: &quot;gatsby build --prefix-paths &amp;&amp; gh-pages -d public&quot;\n}\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>This creates a deploy command that build a static version of your blog and pushes it to GitHub</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add your GitHub repository as the remote origin to your Gatsby Git repository</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">git remote add origin https://&lt;username&gt;.github.com/&lt;repository_name&gt;</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Deploying your Blog:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm run deploy</code></pre></div>\n<p>You will now be able to see your blog at <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;username&gt;.github.io&lt;repository_name&gt;</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"additional-resources-that-may-be-helpful\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#additional-resources-that-may-be-helpful\" aria-label=\"additional resources that may be helpful permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Additional resources that may be helpful</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/sourcing-from-ghost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sourcing from Ghost</a> - Gatsby documentation</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ghost.org/docs/api/v3/gatsby/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Working With Gatsby</a> - Ghost documentation</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/blog/2019-01-14-modern-publications-with-gatsby-ghost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Modern publications with Gatsby &#x26; Ghost</a> - by John O’Nolan</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.bitsrc.io/deploy-a-gatsby-site-on-github-pages-for-free-f18853c1b7a9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Deploy a Gatsby Site on GitHub Pages for Free</a> - by Shaumik Daityari</p>\n<h3 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>In this post, you have accomplished the following:</p>\n</li>\n<li>Install local Ghost crm blog</li>\n<li>Install Gatsby blog using Ghost crm data</li>\n<li>Deploy static Gatsby blog to GitHub Pages</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you have any further questions, please feel free to contact me on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KasperZutterman\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a></p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/deploy-a-ghost-blog-on-github-pages-using-gatsby","tagSlugs":["/tag/technology/","/tag/ghost/","/tag/git-hub-pages/","/tag/gatsby/","/tag/web-development/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-05-10T22:30:00.000Z","description":"If you want to use Ghost as your cms for hosting a blog on GitHub Pages, you need to have a static site generator. We will be using Gatsby to populate the content from our local Ghost installation and deploy it to GitHub Pages.","tags":["Technology","Ghost","GitHub Pages","Gatsby","Web Development"],"title":"Deploy a Ghost blog on GitHub Pages using Gatsby","socialImage":"/media/Ghost-GitHub-Gatsby.png"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/deploy-a-ghost-blog-on-github-pages-using-gatsby"}}}